# SciGate Agent Rules (v2.1)

## JSON Contract v2
Agent 1 outputs: `{ domain, scores: {env, seeds, data, docs, testing, compliance, total}, grade, fixes: [{rank, title, files, dimension, points_recoverable, claude_fix_hint}], gate_blocked, gate_threshold }`

## 5-Agent Pipeline
1. Audit → 6-dimension scoring (17+17+17+17+17+15 = 100)
2. Fix → Claude fix generation + draft PR via VCS adapter
3. Memory → Pattern tracking + leaderboard
4. Regression → Detect score drops, optionally block merge
5. Notify → Fan-out to ntfy, Mattermost, VCS check, badge

## Adapter Pattern
- VCS: `integrations/vcs/base.py` → GitHub, Gitea
- CI: `integrations/ci/base.py` → Jenkins, Woodpecker, GHA
- Notify: `integrations/notify/base.py` → ntfy, Mattermost

## Fix Generation
- `build_skill_context(domain, fix)` constructs Claude system prompt per-fix
- Always strip markdown fences from Claude response before JSON.parse
- Safety filter: never write to files matching train/model/loss/network/arch/backbone/head/encoder/decoder/weights/checkpoint/pretrained

## Policy
- `.scigate/policy.yml` in repo root controls gate, regression gate, channels
- `policy/loader.py` loads and merges with defaults
